{"data":[{"id":"1689076849218117","type":"mrk","contents":"Virtual Table\n======\nOverview\n------\nVirtual table is a representation of various operational information of a Machbase database server in the form of tables.\n\n`V$` To check the types of virtual tables, which start with a character, you can query the **`V$TABLES`** table.\n\nFor more detailed information, you can refer to the Machbase [Manual](https://machbase.atlassian.net/wiki/x/A4g6H).","result":"","status":true,"height":200,"lang":[["markdown","Markdown"],["SQL","SQL"],["javascript","TQL"]],"minimal":true},{"id":"1689076935771632","type":"sql","contents":"SELECT * FROM V$TABLES;","status":true,"height":52,"lang":[["SQL","SQL"],["markdown","Markdown"],["javascript","TQL"]],"minimal":false,"result":""},{"id":"1689077047051900","type":"mrk","contents":"Key Virtual Tables\n------\n\n**`V$SYSSTAT`** Retrieve system statistics information.","status":true,"height":101,"lang":[["markdown","Markdown"],["SQL","SQL"],["javascript","TQL"]],"minimal":true,"result":""},{"id":"1689077373902596","type":"sql","contents":"select * from V$SYSSTAT;","status":true,"height":48,"lang":[["SQL","SQL"],["markdown","Markdown"],["javascript","TQL"]],"minimal":false,"result":""},{"id":"1689077761179709","type":"mrk","contents":"`V$SYSMEM` Retrieve system memory usage information.","status":true,"height":47,"lang":[["markdown","Markdown"],["SQL","SQL"],["javascript","TQL"]],"minimal":true,"result":""},{"id":"1689077809761267","type":"sql","contents":"SELECT * FROM V$SYSMEM;","status":true,"height":45,"lang":[["SQL","SQL"],["markdown","Markdown"],["javascript","TQL"]],"minimal":false,"result":""},{"id":"1689077878543547","type":"mrk","contents":"`V$STMT` Retrieve the currently executing query statements.","status":true,"height":43,"lang":[["markdown","Markdown"],["SQL","SQL"],["javascript","TQL"]],"minimal":true,"result":""},{"id":"168907791834568","type":"sql","contents":"SELECT * FROM V$STMT;","status":true,"height":54,"lang":[["SQL","SQL"],["markdown","Markdown"],["javascript","TQL"]],"minimal":false,"result":""},{"id":"1689078010613972","type":"mrk","contents":"`V$STORAGE` Retrieve disk usage information.\n\n|Item|Description|\n|------------|--------------------------------------------|\n|DC_TABLE_FILE_SIZE| Data file size of the LOG table.|\n|DC_INDEX_FILE_SIZE| Index file size of the LOG table.|\n|DC_TABLESPACE_DWFILE_SIZE| Double Write file size.|\n|DC_KV_TABLE_FILE_SIZE| Data and index file size of the TAG table.|\n\n","status":true,"height":239,"lang":[["markdown","Markdown"],["SQL","SQL"],["javascript","TQL"]],"minimal":true,"result":""},{"id":"1689079092842398","type":"sql","contents":"SELECT * FROM V$STORAGE;","status":true,"height":52,"lang":[["SQL","SQL"],["markdown","Markdown"],["javascript","TQL"]],"minimal":false,"result":""},{"id":"1689078050195626","type":"sql","contents":"SELECT * FROM V$STORAGE;","status":true,"height":48,"lang":[["SQL","SQL"],["markdown","Markdown"],["javascript","TQL"]],"minimal":true,"result":""},{"id":"1689078291231644","type":"mrk","contents":"`V$STORAGE_DC_VOLATILE_TABLE` Retrieve memory usage of Volatile/Lookup tables.\n\n|Item|Description|\n|------------|--------------------------------------------|\n|MAX_MEM_SIZE| Maximum memory size configured in the settings file.(machbase.conf) - (default 2GB)|\n|CUR_MEM_SIZE| Currently used memory size, in bytes.|","status":true,"height":175,"lang":[["markdown","Markdown"],["SQL","SQL"],["javascript","TQL"]],"minimal":true,"result":""},{"id":"1689079127412380","type":"sql","contents":"SELECT * FROM V$STORAGE_DC_VOLATILE_TABLE;","status":true,"height":41,"lang":[["SQL","SQL"],["markdown","Markdown"],["javascript","TQL"]],"minimal":false,"result":""},{"id":"1689079155455358","type":"mrk","contents":"When you retrieve information about Volatile tables, you can examine various system resource usage and statistical information.","status":true,"height":44,"lang":[["markdown","Markdown"],["SQL","SQL"],["javascript","TQL"]],"minimal":true,"result":""},{"id":"1692769641908840","type":"mrk","contents":"Closing Words\n------\nThrough the use of virtual tables, you can easily check current running queries, disk usage, memory usage, and more.","status":true,"height":200,"lang":[["markdown","Markdown"],["SQL","SQL"],["javascript","TQL"]],"minimal":true,"result":""}]}